trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of versions of the .NET Framework that an application prefers to run on.
If an application can run on multiple versions of the .NET Framework, the versions should be listed in priority order from most preferred to least preferred.

If a version of the .NET Framework listed in the <xref:Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Deployment.ManifestUtilities.CompatibleFrameworkCollection> class is installed on the end-user computer, the application can install and run.
Adds a framework to the <xref href="Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Deployment.ManifestUtilities.CompatibleFramework"></xref> class.
Gets the number of .NET Framework versions listed in the <xref href="Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Deployment.ManifestUtilities.CompatibleFrameworkCollection"></xref> collection.

A <xref href="System.Int32"></xref> object that represents the number of .NET Framework versions listed in the <xref href="Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Deployment.ManifestUtilities.CompatibleFrameworkCollection"></xref> collection.
Gets the enumerator for the collection.
A <xref href="System.Collections.IEnumerator"></xref> interface that can iterate over the collection.
Gets a version of the .NET Framework that an application prefers to run on.
The version of .NET Framework to check for on the end-user computer.
A <xref href="Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Deployment.ManifestUtilities.CompatibleFramework"></xref> object that represents the versions of the .NET Framework that an application prefers to run on.
